snippet.textDisplay: Many people say Billie whispering. IMHO, it's the husky-singing technique, which is not easy to do. I only know a few singers who can sing that way naturally, including Mariah Carey who can alter her voice from husky to powerful so effortlessly (I don't mean to compare Billie and Mariah, they have different styles). People who usually sing with a more powerful voice may struggle when they get challenged to sing huskily, as they tend to sound louder when expressing their feeling with the song or certain part of the lyric.

snippet.textDisplay:
I may only be in my mid twenties, but I've grown up listening to everything from AC/DC, to MJ and Elvis. I'm diverse in taste and have listened to maybe hundreds of artist ranging from classical, dubstep and pop, to rock and metal.
I'm not usually a hardcore fan of popular, mainstream artists but I can tell you this: In the last decade I have never, never heard someone who was as talented as Billie. She's intense, she's soft, her voice is clean and clear and full of emotions. This is a live performance and it sounds better than the studio recordings! To me there was never any doubt - she belongs up there with the big ones like MJ, Elvis and Madonna.
So take it in folks! We've witnessed the birth of a star.

snippet.textDisplay: I'm a 50 yr old that grew up on punk, post-punk and 90s grunge. When I first heard Dave Grohl talk about her, I thought he was full of crap. I've quickly become a fan. I love the reserved, controlled way she sings with big dramatic moments like she does at the end of this. I do think her nails in this performance are ridiculous. And I don't have a problem with the florescent green, but it looks like someone dumped a can of paint on her head. But let me reiterate, I love her music. I love her story. I love the close relationship she has with her brother, both as siblings and as colaberators. She seems to be a completely genuine person and artist. But I feel like she's hiding behind her "look." With the rapid climb from being a normal high school kid to being the biggest pop star in the world, it's understandable. That's not a normal thing. But I really can't wait for the day when she will let it all out. It will be amazing to see!

But I really can't wait for the day when she will let it all out. It will be amazing to see!
